Q10.fix_sketch:
Rust-only fix (Python's json.dumps/repr IS the reference; render.py needs no change). Unlike the regex-dialect findings, full behavioral parity IS achievable here: CPython repr is a deterministic pure function of the f64 bits, and Rust already matches on digit count, so only the midpoint tie-break needs repair.

In crates/clankerprof-core/src/pyjson.rs::format_pyfloat, after extracting (sign, digits, exponent) from format!("{value:e}"), insert an exact midpoint-tie repair before layout:

fn repair_midpoint_tie(value: f64, digits: String, exponent: i32) -> String {
    let last = *digits.as_bytes().last().unwrap() - b'0';
    if last % 2 == 0 || last == 0 { return digits; } // even already, or no lower sibling (carry-cascade ties cannot reach here: flt2dec would have emitted the shorter form)
    let (m, k) = decode_f64(value.abs());            // |value| = m * 2^k exactly, from to_bits(); m <= 2^53, -1074 <= k <= 971
    let s = exponent - digits.len() as i32 + 1;      // candidate = d * 10^s
    // Exact midpoint condition: 2*m*2^k == (2d - 1) * 10^s, moving negative powers across:
    let mut lhs = BigUint::from(2 * m); let mut rhs = two_d_minus_one(&digits);
    if k >= 0 { lhs.shl(k as u32) } else { rhs.shl((-k) as u32) }
    if s >= 0 { rhs.mul_pow10(s as u32) } else { lhs.mul_pow10((-s) as u32) }
    if lhs == rhs { let mut b = digits.into_bytes(); *b.last_mut().unwrap() -= 1; String::from_utf8(b).unwrap() } else { digits }
}

Rationale: CPython (Gay dtoa mode 0, the `j1 == 0 && dig & 1` branch) rounds exact decimal midpoints half-to-even; Rust rounds them half-away, so on a true tie Rust's last digit odd ⇒ decrement to the even lower candidate (never needs a borrow — a rounded-up candidate ending in 0 implies a shorter representation flt2dec would already have chosen; keep the last==0 early-return plus a debug_assert). BigUint = a ~40-line hand-rolled u64-limb helper (mul-by-small, shl, cmp only; magnitudes ≤ ~10^770) to avoid a num-bigint dependency; if maintainers prefer belt-and-braces over the repair, the alternative is porting Gay's mode-0 digit-generation loop wholesale.

